
========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 1: OPTICAL DISC <-> FIBER OPTICS
========================================================================

  Both domains resolve spatial features using diffraction.
  The Airy pattern gives resolution = j11/(pi) * lambda/NA
  = j11/(4*R2) * lambda/NA = 1.22 * lambda/NA
  The mode field area = R2 * MFD^2
  The disc spot area = R2 * spot^2

  DISC SPOT SIZES (1.22 * lambda / NA):
    CD:      2.115 um
    DVD:     1.322 um
    Blu-ray: 0.5813 um

  FIBER MODE FIELD AREAS (R2 * MFD^2):
    SMF-28 @1550: 84.95 um^2
    Blu-ray spot: 0.2654 um^2

  RATIO: fiber mode / BD spot = 320.1
  The fiber carries 320.0x more area than the BD reads.

  If disc had CD NA=0.45: lambda needed = 3.836 um (to match SMF-28 MFD)
  If disc had DVD NA=0.6: lambda needed = 5.115 um (to match SMF-28 MFD)
  If disc had BD NA=0.85: lambda needed = 7.246 um (to match SMF-28 MFD)

  All values >>1 um: no disc technology matches fiber mode size.
  The fiber is a waveguide (confines by total internal reflection),
  the disc is a free-space system (limited by diffraction).
  Same R2, different Z (coordinator).

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 2: SPEAKER CONE <-> PIPE FLOW
========================================================================

  Speaker: volume velocity = Sd * x_dot = R2 * d^2 * piston_velocity
  Pipe:    volume flow rate = R2 * d^2 * mean_velocity
  Same R2*d^2, different Z (acoustic impedance vs fluid viscosity)

  12-inch speaker: d = 0.305 m, Sd = R2*d^2 = 730.6 cm^2
  8-inch speaker: d = 0.203 m, Sd = R2*d^2 = 323.7 cm^2
  6-inch speaker: d = 0.152 m, Sd = R2*d^2 = 181.5 cm^2

  PIPE EQUIVALENTS (same R2*d^2):
    12-inch speaker area = 730.6 cm^2 = pipe with d = 0.305 m
    8-inch speaker area = 323.7 cm^2 = pipe with d = 0.203 m

  HELMHOLTZ RESONANCE:
    f = (c_sound / (8*R2)) * sqrt(R2*d_port^2 / (l_eff * V_box))
    = (c_sound / (2*pi)) * sqrt(pi*d^2/(4*l*V))
    Port: d = 0.076 m, l = 0.15 m, V = 0.05 m^3
    f_Helmholtz = 42.46 Hz

  PIPE FLOW through same diameter (0.076 m) at 1 m/s:
    Q = R2 * d^2 * v = 0.004536 m^3/s = 272.2 liters/min

  VENA CONTRACTA: C_c = pi/(pi+2) = 4*R2/(4*R2+2) = 0.611015
  Jet area after sharp orifice = C_c * R2 * d^2
  For 3-inch orifice: A_jet = 27.72 cm^2 (vs orifice 45.36 cm^2)

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 3: WIRE GAUGE <-> CAPACITOR PLATE
========================================================================

  Wire: R_wire = rho * L / (R2 * d^2)
  Capacitor: C = epsilon_0 * R2 * d^2 / t
  Same R2*d^2, different Z (resistivity vs permittivity)

  AWG 12: d = 2.053 mm, area = R2*d^2 = 3.31 mm^2
    Resistance: rho/(R2*d^2) = 0.005208 ohm/m
    If capacitor (1mm gap): C = eps0*R2*d^2/t = 0.02931 pF

  AWG 14: d = 1.628 mm, area = R2*d^2 = 2.082 mm^2
    Resistance: rho/(R2*d^2) = 0.008283 ohm/m
    If capacitor (1mm gap): C = eps0*R2*d^2/t = 0.01843 pF

  R*C PRODUCT for AWG 12 wire + same-area capacitor:
    R = 0.005208 ohm (1m), C = 0.02931 pF (1mm gap)
    RC = 1.527e-16 seconds
    Note: R2 CANCELS in R*C = (rho*L)/(R2*d^2) * eps0*R2*d^2/t = rho*eps0*L/t
    RC is R2-independent. Like K_J * R_K = 2/e.

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 4: ANTENNA <-> TELESCOPE <-> LITHOGRAPHY
========================================================================

  All three resolve features via diffraction through a circular aperture.
  Resolution = j11/pi * lambda/D = 1.22 * lambda/D
  Effective area = R2 * D^2 * efficiency

  GPS L1 ANTENNA:
    f = 1575.42 MHz, lambda = 0.1903 m
    1m dish: resolution = 0.2322 rad = 13.0 deg
    Geometric area = R2 * D^2 = 0.7854 m^2
    Isotropic Aeff = lambda^2/(16*R2) = 0.002882 m^2

  HUBBLE SPACE TELESCOPE:
    D = 2.4 m, lambda = 550.0 nm
    Resolution = 0.05767 arcsec
    Collecting area = R2 * D^2 = 4.524 m^2

  EUV LITHOGRAPHY:
    lambda = 13.5 nm, NA = 0.33
    Half-pitch ~ 1.22*lambda/(2*NA) = 25.0 nm
    Wafer area = R2 * D^2 = R2 * (0.3)^2 = 706.9 cm^2

  ALL THREE USE: resolution = j11/(4*R2) * lambda/D
  j11 = 3.8317, j11/(4*R2) = 1.2197
  Same Bessel zero, same R2, different Z (RF vs photon vs EUV).

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 5: DWDM CHANNELS <-> RAYLEIGH SCATTERING
========================================================================

  DWDM uses lambda ~ 1550 nm in the Rayleigh scattering minimum.
  Rayleigh loss = A/lambda^4 where A contains (8*R2)^4.
  The scattering cross section: sigma ~ (8*R2/lambda)^4 * r^6 * (n^2-1)^2/(n^2+2)^2

  C-band center (lambda = 1550.0 nm): Rayleigh loss = 0.1386 dB/km
  C-band edge (lambda = 1530.0 nm): Rayleigh loss = 0.146 dB/km
  L-band center (lambda = 1590.0 nm): Rayleigh loss = 0.1252 dB/km
  O-band (lambda = 1310.0 nm): Rayleigh loss = 0.2716 dB/km

  The (8*R2/lambda)^4 factor at 1550 nm vs 1310 nm:
    (1310/1550)^4 = 0.5102
    1550 nm has 49.0% lower Rayleigh loss than 1310 nm

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 6: QED EXPANSION PARAMETER <-> INFORMATION DENSITY
========================================================================

  The QED perturbation series expands in alpha/(4*R2) = alpha/pi.
  Each power adds one more loop integral, each loop carries R4 = pi^2/32.

  Disc information density is set by spot area = R2 * (1.22*lambda/NA)^2.
  The connection: both are bounded by how finely R2-scale geometry can resolve.

  alpha/(4*R2) = alpha/pi = 0.0023228195
  This is the QED expansion parameter: each loop costs this factor.

  CD: spot = 2115.0 nm, spot_area = R2*spot^2 = 3.512 um^2, ~28.5 Mbit/cm^2
  DVD: spot = 1322.0 nm, spot_area = R2*spot^2 = 1.372 um^2, ~72.9 Mbit/cm^2
  Blu-ray: spot = 581.3 nm, spot_area = R2*spot^2 = 0.2654 um^2, ~377.0 Mbit/cm^2

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 7: ION IMPLANT DOPING <-> GAUSSIAN BEAM PROFILE
========================================================================

  Ion implant profile: N(x) = (dose/sqrt(8*R2*sigma^2)) * exp(-x^2/(2*sigma^2))
  Gaussian beam:       I(r) = (P/sqrt(8*R2*w^2)) * exp(-r^2/(2*w^2))
  Same R2 normalization, different Z (dose vs power, depth vs radius).

  ION IMPLANT (50nm straggle, 10^15/cm^2 dose):
    Peak concentration = dose/sqrt(8*R2*sigma^2) = 7.979e+19 /cm^3

  GAUSSIAN BEAM (5um waist, 1mW):
    Peak intensity = P/(R2*w^2*4) = P/(pi*w^2) = 5.093e+4 kW/m^2

  TRANSLATION: both peaked distributions normalized by 1/sqrt(8*R2*sigma^2)
  or R2*w^2. The shape is Gaussian. The R2 factor is the circular integration.

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 8: THE R2 CANCELLATION MAP
========================================================================

  R2 appears in every circular-to-rectilinear conversion.
  R2 CANCELS in the highest-precision measurements.
  This is the structural theorem from DATA-1 Section 22.

  Observable           Formula                        R2 Status    Precision
  -------------------- ------------------------------ ------------ ------------
  K_J * R_K            2e/h * h/e^2 = 2/e             CANCELS      verified to 10^-8
  G_0 * R_K            2e^2/h * h/e^2 = 2             CANCELS      exact by construction
  R_inf formula        alpha^2*m_e*c/(2h)             CANCELS      13 digits
  a_0 * alpha          hbar/(m_e*c)                   CANCELS      12 digits
  E_Hartree            m_e*c^2*alpha^2                R2-FREE      10 digits
  Phi_0^2/R_K          h^2/e^2 * e^2/h = h            REAPPEARS    exact

  PATTERN: R2-free observables are measurable to 10^-10 or better.
  R2-dependent observables (engineering) are limited to ~10^-6.
  Level 1 (R2 structure) is confirmed by universality.
  Level 2 (parameters) lives in the R2-free quantities.

========================================================================
  TRANSLATION 9: ALL R2*d^2 EQUATIONS — ONE TABLE
========================================================================

  Every engineering equation where area = R2 * d^2 appears.
  Same R2, different Z (domain coordinator).

  Domain               R2 Equation                      Coordinator Z        Precision
  -------------------- -------------------------------- -------------------- ------------
  Pipe flow            Q = R2*d^2 * v                   velocity v           Coriolis: 0.05%
  Drag force           F = 0.5*rho*v^2*R2*d^2*Cd        drag coeff Cd        Wind tunnel: 1%
  Orifice flow         q = Cd*R2*d^2*sqrt(2dP/rho)      discharge Cd         ISO 5167: 0.5%
  Capacitor            C = eps0*R2*d^2/t                permittivity eps     pF precision
  Poynting flux        P = S*R2*d^2                     irradiance S         Antenna: 0.1 dB
  Antenna aperture     A = eta*R2*D^2                   efficiency eta       Calibrated
  Beam cross-sec       A = R2*d^2                       none (pure geom)     Laser: um
  Thermal radiation    Q = eps*sig*T^4*R2*d^2           emissivity eps       Pyrometer: 1%
  Sound intensity      I = P/(16*R2*r^2)                1/r^2 spreading      SPL: 0.5 dB
  Wire resistance      R = rho*L/(R2*d^2)               resistivity rho      Handbook: 0.1%
  Speaker cone         Sd = R2*d_eff^2                  none (pure geom)     Measured: 5%
  Fiber mode           A = R2*MFD^2                     mode confinement     Corning: 5%
  Disc spot            A = R2*(1.22*lam/NA)^2           diffraction          Standard
  Wafer area           A = R2*D^2                       none (pure geom)     SEMI: exact
  Gaussian beam        A = R2*w0^2 (at waist)           beam parameter       Laser: um

  15 domains. Same R2. Different Z.
  The Z (coordinator) is what makes each department different.
  R2 is what makes them the same.

