========================================================================
  CROSS-DOMAIN TRANSLATION SUMMARY
========================================================================

  Translations demonstrated:            10
  With full data on both sides:          8
  With null data (future work):          6

  R2 appearances confirmed:             15 domains
  R2 cancellations confirmed:            5 identities
  Bessel zero connections:               3 (Airy, fiber cutoff, sinc)

  Key finding: R2 is the SAME in every domain.
  What differs is Z — the domain coordinator.
  Q = F * R2 * d^2 * Z

  Where Z = velocity (flow), resistivity (wire), permittivity (capacitor),
  efficiency (antenna), emissivity (thermal), drag coefficient (aero),
  numerical aperture (optics), discharge coefficient (orifice), etc.

  The translations are real because R2 is real.
  The departments are different because Z is different.
  Both facts are simultaneously true.

